8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 394, L.D. 626, “An Act to Explicitly
10 Allow the Department of Corrections to Charge Room and Board to Residents Who
11 Perform Remote Work in Detention and Correctional Facilities and to Amend the Laws
12 Governing Rehabilitative Programs”
13 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1 in paragraph D in subparagraph (1) in the
14 last line (page 1, line 25 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "transportation" the
15 following: ', not to exceed 10% of a resident's work release earnings'
16 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 1 in paragraph E in subparagraph (1) in the
17 last line (page 1, line 33 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "income." the following:
18 'The cost of room and board may not exceed 10% of the resident's work release or remote
19 work earnings.'
20 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
21 number to read consecutively.
22 SUMMARY
2233 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, codifies current
2244 Department of Corrections rules by explicitly stating the department can charge up to 10%
2255 of a resident's work release earnings for transportation for residents participating in work
2266 release and up to 10% of a resident's work release or remote work earnings for the cost of
2277 room and board for residents participating in work release or remote work.
